  displayName: Aswang
  description: Among the most feared figures in Philippine folklore, the aswang is
    commonly described not as a single being but as a category of predatory shapeshifters
    associated with night hunting, secrecy, and deception. Regional traditions present
    many forms and habits, yet most accounts agree on its unnatural hunger and ability
    to hide behind ordinary appearances. In cultural memory, the aswang often represents
    social fear of the unseen danger within familiar communities.
